# Deploy always (Yash Gallery ERP)

Production deploys via **GitHub Actions** (`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`) on **push to `origin/main`** (self-hosted runner at `/root/app`).

**After you implement or fix anything in this repo that should reach production:**

1. Commit with a clear message.
2. Run **`git push origin main`** (request `git_write`, `network`, and `all` if needed so `.git` and push work).
3. Do **not** stop with only local commits — the user expects the VPS to update.

**Skip push** only when the user explicitly asks for local-only work or a branch/PR flow.

**Manual deploy:** In GitHub → Actions → “Deploy to VPS” → **Run workflow** (requires `workflow_dispatch` in the workflow file).
